headline: A Look At Synchrony Financial (SYF) Valuation After Trump’s Proposed Credit Card Rate Cap
summary: President Trump’s proposal to cap credit card interest rates at 10% for a year puts a spotlight on Synchrony Financial (SYF), whose private label credit card business depends heavily on interest income and risk pricing. See our latest analysis for Synchrony Financial. The regulatory headlines appear to have fed into recent volatility, with a 1 day share price return of a 5.13% decline and a 30 day share price return of a 10.16% decline, even as the 1 year total shareholder return of 11.46%...

headline: Will Lower Active Accounts Impact Synchrony's Q4 Earnings Potential?
summary: SYF heads into Q4 with higher margins and purchase volumes, but declining active accounts and average interest-earning assets cloud earnings upside.
